view.name: Wildland Search and Rescue Missions by NYS Forest Rangers: Beginning 2012
view.attribution: NYS Department of Environmental Conservation, Division of Forest Protection
view.description: Search and Rescue incidents for which the Division of Forest Protection has responded

columns.name: INCIDENT NUMBER
columns.description: Number assigned to each new incident

columns.name: INCIDENT REGION
columns.description: NYSDEC Region that has jurisdiction over the incident:  Region 1: (Long Island) Nassau and Suffolk counties Region; 2: (New York City) Brooklyn, Bronx, Manhattan, Queens and Staten Island; Region 3: (Lower Hudson Valley) Dutchess, Orange, Putnam, Rockland, Sullivan, Ulster and Westchester* counties; Region 4: (Capital Region/Northern Catskills) Albany, Columbia, Delaware, Greene, Montgomery, Otsego, Rensselaer, Schenectady and Schoharie counties; Region 5: (Eastern Adirondacks/Lake Champlain) Clinton, Essex, Franklin, Fulton, Hamilton, Saratoga, Warren and Washington counties; Region 6: (Western Adirondacks/Eastern Lake Ontario) Herkimer, Jefferson, Lewis, Oneida and St. Lawrence counties; Region 7: (Central New York) Broome, Cayuga, Chenango, Cortland*, Madison, Onondaga, Oswego, Tioga and Tompkins counties; Region 8: (Western Finger Lakes) Chemung, Genesee, Livingston, Monroe, Ontario, Orleans, Schuyler, Seneca, Steuben, Wayne and Yates counties; Region 9: (Western New York) Allegany, Chautauqua, Cattaraugus, Erie, Niagara and Wyoming counties

columns.name: RESPONSE TYPE
columns.description: Nature of the incident: Fugitive Search, Search, Rescue, or Recovery

columns.name: INCIDENT START DATE
columns.description: Date NYS Forest Rangers were first deployed to the incident

columns.name: INCIDENT START TIME
columns.description: Time NYS Forest Rangers were first deployed to the incident

columns.name: SUBJECT NUMBER
columns.description: Number in party being searched for

columns.name: SUBJECT GENDER
columns.description: Subject’s gender

columns.name: SUBJECT AGE
columns.description: Subject’s Age

columns.name: SUBJECT STATE
columns.description: State Subject resides in

columns.name: SUBJECT COUNTRY
columns.description: Subject's country of origin and/or legal residence

columns.name: ACTIVITY
columns.description: The primary activity the subject was undertaking in need of a search or rescue response: aircraft, biking, boating, camping, chainsaw climbing: rock/ice, criminal, despondent, fishing, flood victim, hiking, horseback riding, hunting, motor vehicle, off road vehicle/atv/, runaway, Skiing, snowmobile, stranded, swimming, walking, whitewater

columns.name: SITUATION
columns.description: The situation the subject was in when help was requested: Fugitive, Illness, Injured, Lost, Missing, Overdue, Stranded

columns.name: LOCATION FOUND LATITUDE
columns.description: Latitude in WGS 84/NAD 83 format subject’s location

columns.name: LOCATION FOUND LONGITUDE
columns.description: Longitude in WGS 84/NAD 83 format subject’s location

columns.name: LOCATION FOUND ELEVATION
columns.description: Elevation at which the subject was located

columns.name: FOUND IN SEARCH AREA
columns.description: Was the subject located in the established search area: (YES/NO)

columns.name: TECHNIQUE
columns.description: The method by which the subject was rescued or recovered: Airboat, Aircraft evacuation, Assist/own power, Carry out by foot, Dive team, Evacuation by animal, High Angle, Swiftwater, Technical Rope, Vehicle/boat evacuation

columns.name: NUMBER OF RANGERS INVOLVED
columns.description: The total number of DEC Forest Rangers involved in the incident

columns.name: OTHER AGENCY INVOLVEMENT
columns.description: Agencies other than DEC involved (YES/NO)

columns.name: LAST KNOWN POINT LAND CLASS
columns.description: Land classification of the land of the subject's last known location (LKP): Conservation, Easement, County Land, DEC Campground, Federal Land, Forest Preserve, Native People's Land, OPRHP State Land, Other DEC Land, Other Municipal Land, Private Land, State Forests, Wildlife Management Area

columns.name: LAST KNOWN POINT STATE LAND NAME
columns.description: Name of the State Land unit, if the incident search area is within a State Land unit

columns.name: LAST KNOWN POINT COUNTY
columns.description: County of the Subject's last known point

columns.name: LAST KNOWN POINT MUNICIPALITY
columns.description: Municipality of the Subject's last known point

columns.name: INCIDENT ADIRONDACK PARK
columns.description: Did incident occur within the geographic boundary of the Adirondack Park (YES/NO)

columns.name: INCIDENT CATSKILL PARK
columns.description: Did incident occur within the geographic boundary of the Catskill Park (YES/NO)

columns.name: INCIDENT CLOSED DATE
columns.description: Date the incident was completed and demobilized

columns.name: INCIDENT CLOSED TIME
columns.description: Time the incident was completed and demobilized

columns.name: Location
columns.description: Open Data/Socrata-generated geocoding information.

Disclaimers.Limitations: The information reflects S&R missions based on subject activity.  Older information will be limited by less activities captured in past.  Open missions with no subject found.
